Class Book

java.lang.Object
Resource
Book
public class Book
extends Resource
Book Represents a book within the library that inherits from the Resource class. This class adds an ISBN for the book, the edition, a string representing damages and the current LibraryMember holding the book. A book can be held by 0 or 1 LibraryMembers.
Since:
2020-11-27
Version:
1.0
Author:
James Welsh

    • setCurrentHolder

      public void setCurrentHolder​(LibraryMember libraryMember)
      Changes the current owner to a new one, or if there is no owner (i.e. currentHolder is set to null) an owner is attributed to the book. It will not let the libraryMember object be set to null. This can be done using the 'makeBookAvailable()' function.
      Parameters:
      libraryMember - The member of the library who the ownership of the book is transferred to.

    • printResourceDetails

    • isAvailable

      public boolean isAvailable()
      Checks if a book is currently on loan to a library member.
      Returns:
      returns true if the book is in the library and false otherwise.

    • addDamages

      public void addDamages​(java.lang.String damages)
      Updates the string that describes all damages to the book. If the book has no damages it simply adds the damage report, otherwise the string is preceded by a commas to separate all the damage descriptions into a list.
      Parameters:
      damages - A text description of the new damages to the book to append to the damage description.

    • makeBookAvailible

      public void makeBookAvailible()
      Frees the book from it current owner and makes the book available to other library members to take out.
